Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

### 1. Platform-specific tests (Windows only)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)] // MSTest v3.8+ built-in
public void Registry_ReadsValue() { ... }

// Or manually:
[TestMethod]
public void Registry_ReadsValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
    // ...
}
```

### 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedOutput() { ... }
```

Then exclude in CI via filter: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

Or conditionally at runtime:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");
    // ...
}
```

### 3. Flaky external API (retry)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // MSTest v3.8+ — retries up to 3 times on failure
public void Weather_ReturnsForecast() { ... }
```

> **Tip:** Prefer mocking the weather API in unit tests. Use `[Retry]` only for integration tests where you intentionally hit the real service.

### 4. Cleanup even on failure

Use `try/finally`, `IDisposable`, or `[TestCleanup]`:

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
        => _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();

    [TestCleanup] // Runs even if the test fails
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile_WritesOutput()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        // ... assert something — Cleanup runs regardless
    }
}
```

**Summary of MSTest features used:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| Platform-specific | `[OSCondition]` or `Assert.Inconclusive` |
| Skip in CI | `[TestCategory]` + filter, or env-var check |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(n)]` (v3.8+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` or `IDisposable` |
